2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the uplink of a cell-free massive MIMO system, which involves networking and internet architecture concepts such as access points and backhaul. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a new algorithm for C&F in a system with a large number of distributed access points, which involves systems and control concepts such as optimization and performance analysis. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the system throughput of a cell-free massive MIMO system, which involves multimedia concepts such as data transmission and reception. 
5. cs.COM (Computational Complexity): The paper proposes a low complexity coefficient selection algorithm for C&F, which involves computational complexity concepts such as algorithm design and analysis.
